.TH LUAINSTALLER 1 "July 2026" "luainstaller 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
luai, luainstaller \- package Lua applications for a matching runtime environment
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B luai
.B \-h
.br
.B luai
.B \-v
.br
.B luai
.BR \-a | \-t | \-b
.I entry.lua
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ \-\- " args..." ]
.PP
.B luainstaller
.BR help | version
.br
.B luainstaller
.BR analyze | trace | build
.I entry.lua
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ \-\- " args..." ]
.br
.B luainstaller logs
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B luainstaller
discovers Lua
.B require
dependencies and builds a native launcher containing the entry script and
pure-Lua modules. Lua C modules and, where required, the Lua shared runtime are
placed beside the launcher in an inspectable directory bundle.
.PP
The output is not a universal executable. The target must match the selected
operating-system family, CPU architecture, system ABI, and Lua ABI. External
shared libraries required by Lua C modules are not copied automatically.
.PP
.B luai
and
.B luainstaller
call the same Lua API but use separate command grammars. The short command uses
flags; the descriptive command uses words. Their syntax is intentionally not
interchangeable.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B luai \-a
Analyze dependencies.
.TP
.B luai \-t
Print dependency resolution decisions and compatibility notes.
.TP
.B luai \-b
Build an onedir or onefile bundle.
.TP
.B luainstaller analyze
Analyze dependencies.
.TP
.B luainstaller trace
Print dependency resolution decisions and compatibility notes.
.TP
.B luainstaller build
Build an onedir or onefile bundle.
.TP
.B luainstaller logs
Read persistent diagnostic records.
.TP
.B luai \-h
Print short-command help.
.TP
.B luainstaller help
Print descriptive-command help.
.TP
.BR "luai \-v" ", " "luainstaller version"
Print version information.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-dir ", " \-\-onedir
Build an inspectable directory. This is the default.
.TP
.BR \-\-file ", " \-\-onefile
Build a self-extracting executable from a staged onedir bundle.
.TP
.BR \-o " " path ", " \-\-out " " path
Set the output directory or onefile executable path.
.TP
.BI \-\-include " path"
Add a Lua source file not found by automatic discovery. Repeatable.
.TP
.BI \-\-exclude " value"
Exclude an exact path, basename, or path suffix. Repeatable. Exclusions take
precedence over discovery and manual includes.
.TP
.BR \-d " " mode ", " \-\-discovery-mode " " mode
Use
.BR static ,
.BR runtime ,
or
.B manual
dependency discovery.
.TP
.B \-\-no-depscan
Disable automatic discovery; equivalent to manual mode.
.TP
.BI \-\-max-deps " number"
Set the maximum discovered Lua source dependency count. Default: 36.
.TP
.BI \-\-lua " path"
Select the Lua interpreter used by runtime discovery.
.TP
.BI \-\-target-os " os"
Select
.BR linux ,
.BR macos ,
or
.B windows
build profile.
.TP
.BI \-\-lua-prefix " path"
Select the Lua headers/runtime prefix used by profiled targets.
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Print additional trace or bundle counts.
.TP
.B \-\-
Pass the remaining arguments to the entry during runtime dependency discovery.
They are not stored as executable defaults.
.SS Log options
.TP
.BI \-\-limit " number"
Limit returned log records to a positive integer.
.TP
.BI \-\-level " level"
Filter by
.BR debug ,
.BR info ,
.BR warning ,
.BR error ,
or
.BR success .
.TP
.B \-\-asc
Print oldest records first. The default is newest first.
.SH DISCOVERY MODES
.TP
.B static
Parse literal require calls without running the application. Literal Lua string
escapes are decoded. Computed names return
.BR DynamicRequireError .
.TP
.B runtime
Execute the entry under a temporary require tracer. Only executed branches are
observed. Successfully loaded modules are retained; missing modules caught by
the application with
.B pcall
remain optional.
.TP
.B manual
Start with no automatic dependencies and use repeated
.B \-\-include
options.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Analyze, trace, then build onedir:
.PP
.nf
luai \-a app/main.lua \-\-max-deps 120
luai \-t app/main.lua \-\-max-deps 120
luai \-b \-\-dir app/main.lua \-o build/app \-\-max-deps 120
env \-i PATH=/usr/bin:/bin build/app/app
.fi
.PP
Build onefile after onedir succeeds:
.PP
.nf
luainstaller build \-\-file app/main.lua \-o build/app-onefile
.fi
.PP
Trace a computed dependency path with build-time arguments:
.PP
.nf
luai \-t app/main.lua \-d runtime \-\- profile_a input.json
.fi
.PP
Cross-build a Windows x86_64 profile from Linux:
.PP
.nf
luainstaller build app/main.lua \-\-target-os windows \\
  \-\-lua-prefix /opt/windows-lua54 \-o build/app
.fi
.SH OUTPUT
An onedir bundle contains the native executable and a hidden
.B .luai
directory with generated C source, manifest, output marker, and native files.
Rebuilds occur in a private sibling staging directory. An existing recognized
bundle is preserved while compilation runs. Final installation uses sequential
directory renames, with a brief visibility gap, and is not crash-atomic.
.PP
Onefile extracts a content-addressed onedir payload below the user temporary
directory. POSIX caches are separated by effective user ID and require
owner-only permissions. Unsafe paths, parent symlinks, and Windows reparse
points are rejected.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B LUAI_LUA
Default interpreter for runtime discovery and source-installed wrappers.
.TP
.B LUAI_LUA_PREFIX
Default Lua prefix for profiled builds.
.TP
.B LUAI_TARGET_OS
Default target profile when the API option is absent.
.TP
.B LUAI_WINDOWS_CC
Windows cross-compiler command. Default:
.BR x86_64-w64-mingw32-gcc .
.TP
.B LUA_PATH, LUA_CPATH
Search paths used during dependency discovery. Clear them when verifying that a
finished bundle does not rely on host modules.
.TP
.B TMPDIR
Temporary root for runtime discovery and POSIX onefile extraction.
.TP
.B HOME, USERPROFILE
Home directory used for persistent logs.
.TP
.B NO_COLOR, CI
Disable interactive color output.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.luainstaller/logs.lua
Persistent diagnostic records on POSIX when
.B HOME
is set.
.TP
.I output/.luai/manifest.lua
Inspectable bundle manifest.
.TP
.I output/.luai/generated-output.txt
Generated-output ownership and hash marker.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Zero indicates success. Command parsing, analysis, build, extraction, or child
application failure returns nonzero.
.SH INSTALLATION
.nf
luarocks install luainstaller
.fi
.PP
From a source checkout:
.PP
.nf
sh tools/install-source.sh \-\-prefix "$HOME/.local"
.fi
.SH LUA API
The module
.B luainstaller
exports
.BR analyze ,
.BR trace ,
.BR compatibility ,
.BR bundle ,
.BR getLogs ,
and
.BR clearLogs .
Operations return a table with
.B ok=true
or a structured
.B error
table containing at least
.B type
and
.BR message .
